==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eugenol
<hw>Eu"ge*nol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Eugenia</ets>
+ <ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless, aromatic,
liquid hydrocarbon, <chform>C10H12O2</chform> resembling the phenols,
and hence also called <altname>eugenic acid</altname>. It is found in
the oils of pimento and cloves.</def> <-- used as an analgesic in
dentistry. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eugeny</ent>⟦br⟧
